text.section:
The Executive Director shall:
Direct and supervise the administrative affairs and activities of the Authority in accordance with its regulations and policies;
Attend all meetings of the Authority;
Keep minutes of all proceedings of the Authority;
Approve:
All accounts for salaries, per diem payments, and allowable expenses of the Authority and its employees and consultants; and
All expenses incidental to the operation of the Authority;
Report and make recommendations to the Authority on the merits and status of any management plan for the Heritage Area; and
Perform any other duty that the Authority requires for carrying out the provisions of this subtitle.
